item.dc:creator: @bakatool bakatool
item.description:
@bakatool wrote:

go to start button and in run type in cmd
in the newly opened command prompt u gotta type ipconfig /all

and look for any ip’s similar to 192.168 or 168.192 something similar to that and just go to your ip as a website
http://192.168.whatever/
99% of routers have a menu there where u can portfoward
